es a better understanding of the processes of secularization in Turkey as well as elsewhere in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aIslam and statezTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aSecularismzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014412340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300144123423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300144123/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles